properties.name: Borumba Pumped Hydro Energy Storage
properties.description: Large-scale, long-duration pumped hydro energy storage project with up to 2,000 MW for up to 24 hours (48,000 MWh) capacity.

properties.name: Stony Creek Wind Farm
properties.description: Proposed wind farm in the North Burnett Region of Queensland, with an expected capacity of up to 166 MW and up to 23 wind turbines.

properties.name: Specimen Hill Wind Farm
properties.description: Proposed wind farm in Central Queensland. Expected capacity of up to 336 MW and 56 turbines.

properties.name: Tarong West Wind Farm
properties.description: Proposed wind farm (formerly known as Iron Leaf Wind Farm) located in Ironpot, Queensland. Expected capacity up to 436.5 MW with 97 turbines.

properties.name: Coopers Gap Wind Farm
properties.description: Operating wind farm located between Dalby and Kingaroy, Queensland. Has 453MW of capacity with 123 turbines. Second greenfield project developed by Tilt Renewables.

properties.name: Wambo Wind Farm
properties.description: Two stage wind farm located in the Western Downs. Stage One is under construction and will consist of 42 turbines generating up to 252 MW. Stage Two is due to commence construction in 2024 with a further 41 turbines with capacity up to 254.2 MW. Stanwell Corporate have backed the project with $455.8 million investment from the Queensland Government through the Queensland Renewable Energy and Hydrogen Jobs Fund.

properties.name: Chinchilla Solar Farm
properties.description: Proposed solar farm in Western Downs, Queensland. Expected capacity up to 100 MW.
